title: David Bowie - 1995-10-16 Denver
description:
Here is a nice Bowie concert. Check my account for more classic bootlegs.

Please enjoy, share with friends and please seed :)


David Bowie - 9510-16 - Denver

Live at the McNichols Arena, Denver, CO, USA on 16th October 1995

From an old and dusted archive.

Audio source: Audience recording
Linage: AUD(DAT/CLONE) ---> CDR ---> WAV ---> FLAC 8 ---> MWP
Number of discs: 2
Artwork: none
Total running time: 73m 12s / 24m 00s

Info: Again a special requested.

This recording is sourced from DAT clone and includes the NIN/Bowie and Bowie sets. The sound
quality of this set is (again) pretty good, but lacks some bass. Bowie is in very good mood, 
giving a very decent performance - a good setlist as well.

I am not sure if this is the same source as "They're Winning Next Door", which appeared a couple
of years after I got this (nameless) set.

As always, enjoy it!
